  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nI'm trying to do is expose port 13000 via ipv6. \r\nMy ISP supports ONLY ipv6. I've set up port forwarding correctly (it works for ssh) but port 13000 is not reachable.\r\n\r\nWhen I add `p2p-local-ip: \"::\"` to my prysm-beacon.yaml I get errors in the validator client and it crashes (see below error).\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nNo\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\nTry to expose an ipv6 address via `--p2p-local-ip`\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n<pre><code>\r\nlevel=fatal msg=\"Failed to start discovery\" error=\"could not create listener: could not listen to UDP: listen udp4 [::]:12000: address ::: non-IPv4 address\" prefix=p2p\r\n\r\nlevel=fatal msg=\"Could not determine if beacon chain started: could not setup beacon chain ChainStart streaming client: rpc error: code = Unavailable desc = \r\nconnection error: desc = \"transport: Error while dialing dial tcp 127.0.0.1:4000: connect: connection refused\"\" prefix=validator\r\n\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Operating System:**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nUbuntu LTS\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\ntime=\"2021-01-20 12:40:13\" level=info msg=\"Starting beacon node\" prefix=node version=\"Prysm/v1.1.0/9b367b36fc12ecf565ad649209aa2b5bba8c7797. Built at: 2021-01-18 19:47:14+00:00\"\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n",
